to 1\n        min_start_value = 1\n        # Initialize the current step by step sum\n        current_sum = 0\n        \n        # Iterate through the nums array\n        for num in nums:\n            # Update the current step by step sum\n            current_sum += num\n            # If the current step by step sum is less than 1,\n            # we need to increase the start value\n            if current_sum < 1:\n                min_start_value = max(min_start_value, 1 - current_sum)\n        \n        return min_start_value\n```\n\nThis solution iterates through the `nums` array, maintaining a running sum (`current_sum`). It checks if at any point the running sum is less than 1, and if so, calculates the required `startValue` to ensure the running sum never goes below 1. The `min_start_value` is adjusted accordingly.", "estimated_date": 1586649600000}